oc:kn_51c33438 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "Requires office-mcp server with create_docx and create_pptx tools for document output generation." .

oc:kn_86f37c31 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When documenting or enforcing logo usage rules" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never alter logo proportions, rotate logos, change colors, add effects, or place logos on busy backgrounds." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Logo misuse is the most common brand consistency violation and undermines brand recognition." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_87ea15de a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating the full brand guidelines document" ;
    oc:directiveContent """# {BrandName} Brand Guidelines

## Table of Contents
1. Brand Overview (Mission, Vision, Values, Personality, Target Audience)
2. Logo Usage (Variations, Clear Space, Minimum Sizes, Colors, Don'ts)
3. Color Palette (Primary/Secondary/Accent with Hex/RGB/CMYK/Pantone)
4. Typography (Primary/Secondary Fonts, Sizes, Line Heights)
5. Imagery (Photography, Illustration, Iconography)
6. Voice & Tone (Voice definition, Tone by Context, Writing Guidelines)
7. Applications (Business Cards, Email, Social Media, Presentations)
8. Do's and Don'ts""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "BrandName" .

oc:kn_9045eada a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining color palette and typography combinations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "All text color combinations must meet WCAG 2.1 AA contrast requirements: 4.5:1 for normal text and 3:1 for large text." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Accessibility compliance is a legal and ethical requirement for brand materials in most contexts." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_91e1096f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating brand guidelines from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Gather brand inputs (logo files, existing colors, fonts, brand personality adjectives) 2. Fill the 8-section template starting with Brand Overview 3. Define logo variations and clear space rules 4. Specify color palette in all formats (Hex/RGB/CMYK/Pantone) with accessibility checks 5. Document typography hierarchy with sizes for desktop and mobile 6. Describe imagery style and iconography specs 7. Define voice/tone with context-specific examples 8. Add application specs (business cards, social media, email signatures) 9. Compile Do's and Don'ts quick reference 10. Generate DOCX or PPTX output" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_b1a68432 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining the color palette section" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Color specifications should always be provided in multiple formats (Hex, RGB, CMYK, Pantone) to cover both digital and print use cases." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different production methods require different color systems; omitting any format causes reproduction errors." .

oc:kn_e98835f1 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any brand guidelines document" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Brand guidelines must cover 8 core sections: Brand Overview, Logo Usage, Color Palette, Typography, Imagery, Voice & Tone, Applications, and Do's and Don'ts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Complete coverage ensures consistency across all brand touchpoints and prevents ambiguity for anyone using the brand assets." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

